hat were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Paryking was born in 1456, in Cornwall, England. He married Mrs William Paryking in 1480, in Cornwall, England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1511, in his hometown, at the age of 55."},"et":{"1456–1511":"1456–1511","1460–Female":"1460–Surnud","1478–1538":"1478–1538","1456":"1456","1478":"1478","1511":"1511","1460":"1460","1480":"1480","1538":"1538","St Stephen in Brannel, Cornwall, England":"St Stephen, Cornwall, England","Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, England"},"fi":{"1456–1511":"1456–1511","1460–Female":"1460–Kuollut","1478–1538":"1478–1538","1456":"1456","1478":"1478","1511":"1511","1460":"1460","1480":"1480","1538":"1538","St Stephen in Brannel, Cornwall, England":"St Stephen, Cornwall, England","Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, England"},"fr":{"1456–1511":"1456–1511","1460–Female":"1460–Décédée","1478–1538":"1478–1538","1456":"1456","1478":"1478","1511":"1511","1460":"1460","1480":"1480","1538":"1538","St Stephen in Brannel, Cornwall, England":"St Stephen, Cornouailles, Angleterre","Cornwall, England":"Cornouailles, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"William Paryking est né en 1456, à Cornouailles, Angleterre. Il a épousé Mrs William Paryking en 1480, à Cornouailles, Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille. Il est décédé en 1511, dans sa ville natale, à l’âge de 55 ans."},"de":{"1456–1511":"1456–1511","1460–Female":"1460–Verstorben","1478–1538":"1478–1538","1456":"1456","1478":"